  "text": "The Kubernetes API server admission controller pipeline is implemented across multiple Go source files in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository. The core admission framework is located in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/, while Kubernetes-specific plugins are registered in pkg/kubeapiserver/.\n\n## Core Admission Framework\n\n**Interface Definition and Registration** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/interfaces.go):\n- Defines the `Interface` interface with `Handles()` method for checking operation support\n- Defines `MutationInterface` with `Admit()` method for mutating plugins\n- Defines `ValidationInterface` with `Validate()` method for validating plugins\n- Defines `Attributes` interface containing request information and `ReinvocationContext` for tracking re-invocations\n\n**Plugin Management** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugins.go):\n- `Plugins` registry manages admission plugin registration and instantiation\n- `NewFromPlugins()` method creates the admission chain from a list of plugin names\n- Separates mutating plugins from validating plugins for ordered execution\n\n## Admission Chain Execution\n\n**Chain Implementation** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/chain.go):\n- `chainAdmissionHandler` is a slice of `Interface` implementations that executes plugins sequentially\n- `Admit()` method calls `MutationInterface.Admit()` on each handler that handles the operation\n- `Validate()` method calls `ValidationInterface.Validate()` on each handler in order\n- Returns immediately on first error from any handler\n\n**Re-invocation Support** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/reinvocation.go):\n- `reinvoker` wraps the admission chain to support re-invocation based on `ReinvocationContext`\n- `newReinvocationHandler()` creates this wrapper\n- Calls mutating plugins twice if `ShouldReinvoke()` returns true, supporting webhook reinvocation policies\n\n## Mutating Admission Webhooks\n\n**Webhook Plugin** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/plugin.go):\n- `Plugin` implements `admission.MutationInterface`\n- `Register()` registers the \"MutatingAdmissionWebhook\" plugin\n- `NewMutatingWebhook()` creates instances using `generic.NewWebhook()`\n\n**Configuration Management** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/mutating_webhook_manager.go):\n- `mutatingWebhookConfigurationManager` implements `generic.Source` interface\n- `NewMutatingWebhookConfigurationManager()` creates manager that watches MutatingWebhookConfiguration resources\n- Maintains list of webhook accessors and notifies on changes\n\n**Dispatcher** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/mutating/dispatcher.go):\n- `mutatingDispatcher` implements `generic.Dispatcher` interface\n- `Dispatch()` iterates through webhook list and calls individual webhooks\n- Applies JSON patches from webhook responses to the request object\n- Handles re-invocation markers for webhook re-invocation policy\n\n## Validating Admission Webhooks\n\n**Webhook Plugin** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/plugin.go):\n- `Plugin` implements `admission.ValidationInterface`\n- `Register()` registers the \"ValidatingAdmissionWebhook\" plugin\n- `NewValidatingAdmissionWebhook()` creates instances using `generic.NewWebhook()`\n\n**Configuration Management** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/configuration/validating_webhook_manager.go):\n- `validatingWebhookConfigurationManager` implements `generic.Source` interface\n- `NewValidatingWebhookConfigurationManager()` creates manager that watches ValidatingWebhookConfiguration resources\n- Maintains list of webhook accessors and notifies on configuration changes\n\n**Dispatcher** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/validating/dispatcher.go):\n- `validatingDispatcher` implements `generic.Dispatcher` interface\n- `Dispatch()` iterates through webhook list and calls individual webhooks\n- Does not modify the object (read-only validation)\n- Returns rejection errors from webhooks immediately\n\n## Generic Webhook Infrastructure\n\n**Webhook Base** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/webhook.go):\n- `Webhook` type provides common infrastructure for both mutating and validating webhooks\n- `NewWebhook()` creates generic webhooks with configurable source (config manager) and dispatcher\n- Handles webhook client management, authorization checking, and CEL condition evaluation\n\n## Kubernetes-Specific Configuration\n\n**Plugin Registration** (pkg/kubeapiserver/options/plugins.go):\n- `RegisterAllAdmissionPlugins()` registers all kube-apiserver admission plugins\n- `AllOrderedPlugins` defines execution order: mutating plugins first, then validating plugins\n- Mutating webhooks execute before validating webhooks\n- Admission policies (CEL-based) execute in their own positions\n\n**Server Integration** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/admission.go):\n- `AdmissionOptions.ApplyTo()` creates the admission chain and sets it on the server config\n- Initializes all plugin initializers including generic and Kubernetes-specific ones\n- Wraps the chain with metrics decorator via `admissionmetrics.WithStepMetrics()`\n\n## Request Handler Integration\n\nThe admission chain is called at request handling time:\n\n- **Create Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/create.go):\n  - Calls mutating admission via `mutatingAdmission.Admit(ctx, admissionAttributes, scope)`\n  - Calls validating admission via handlers\n\n- **Update Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/update.go):\n  - Calls mutating and validating admission for UPDATE operations\n\n- **Patch Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/patch.go):\n  - Calls mutating and validating admission for PATCH operations\n\n- **Delete Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/delete.go):\n  - Calls admission for DELETE operations\n\n- **REST Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/rest.go):\n  - Calls admission for CONNECT operations\n\n- **Field Manager** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/fieldmanager/admission.go):\n  - `NewManagedFieldsValidatingAdmissionController()` wraps admission to validate managed fields\n\nThe execution order ensures mutating plugins run first to modify the request, followed by validating plugins to verify the final state, with webhook re-invocation support for interdependent webhooks."
